    {
      "id": "PopularPost185224",
      "post_content": "@Banjo: Actually, this thing is way more useful in shutting down TES/TPS. Affinity don't have much of a CMC focus. Much. CMC 2 could make it painful, especially if they opted to run [Naturalize](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Naturalize) over [Krosan Grip](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Krosan Grip) or [Nature's Claim](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Nature's Claim). That does happen to shut down [Arcbound Ravager](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Arcbound Ravager), [Stoneforge Mystic](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Stoneforge Mystic), [Fling](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Fling), [Ethersworn Canonist](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ethersworn Canonist), and [Vault Skirge](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Vault Skirge). Not a bad spread, considering those are pretty key, regardless of which Affinity variant they run.  \nI also like this against Landstill, set it to 2 to kill card advantage. Sure, there are issues getting it out and keeping it out, but time bought is time well spent.   \n  \nAnyways, really math card. Love the filling outta this donut, man. 5/5",
      "posted_by": "ZestuXIII",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost185224\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_post\">@Banjo: Actually, this thing is way more useful in shutting down TES/TPS. Affinity don't have much of a CMC focus. Much. CMC 2 could make it painful, especially if they opted to run <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Naturalize\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Naturalize\">Naturalize</a> over <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Krosan Grip\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Krosan Grip\">Krosan Grip</a> or <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Nature's Claim\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Nature's Claim\">Nature's Claim</a>. That does happen to shut down <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Arcbound Ravager\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Arcbound Ravager\">Arcbound Ravager</a>, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Stoneforge Mystic\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Stoneforge Mystic\">Stoneforge Mystic</a>, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Fling\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Fling\">Fling</a>, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Ethersworn Canonist\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ethersworn Canonist\">Ethersworn Canonist</a>, and <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Vault Skirge\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Vault Skirge\">Vault Skirge</a>. Not a bad spread, considering those are pretty key, regardless of which Affinity variant they run.<br/>I also like this against Landstill, set it to 2 to kill card advantage. Sure, there are issues getting it out and keeping it out, but time bought is time well spent. <br/><br/>Anyways, really math card. Love the filling outta this donut, man. 5/5</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '185224'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy58639\">ZestuXIII</span>\r\n                                (8/4/2011 8:19:16 PM)\r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    Rating:\u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n<div class=\"starRating\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_postRating_starRating\"><img alt=\"0.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"5.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/>\n<br/>\n</div>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    \u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>"
